cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CC 

The paper deals with the problem of joint source-channel coding on a multiple access channel with side information, which is a classic problem in information theory and communication engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the transmission of distributed sources with continuous alphabets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of side information at the sources and decoder suggests the category of cs.SI (Signal Processing and Image Processing). The paper also considers channels with feedback and fading, which are relevant to the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
